free_txt: Bangalore university.

The distorted wave BORN approximation
calculations.  He3 and triton energy spectra were
obtained.
Spectroscopic strengths were extracted for all
the states and were compared with the predictions from
shell-model and quasi-particle core-coupling
calculations.
Optical-model parameters for alpha-particles
deduced from elastic scattering at 45 MeV and He3 and
tritons from investigated reactions.
A del'Ta E-E solid state detector
counter telescope was used to identify the reaction
products: He3 and tritons.  The del'Ta E detector was a
250-mum silicon surface barrier detector while
the E detector was a 5-mm lithium-drifted silicon
detector.
. The estimated error on target thickness.
The variable energy cyclotron.
A self-supporting 1.26 mg/cm**2 thick natural silicon
target, 92.23% of Si-28, 4.68% of Si-29 and 3.10%  of
Si-30, was used. The target was prepared by chemical
etching of detector-quality material. The target
thickness was determined by normalizing the yield from
silicon target with that from a 0.96 mg/cm**2 thick AL
target whose thickness was measured accurately using
the energy loss of alpha particles from a Am-241 source
and also by weighing.
